✅ Full Flow

1.Start Android emulator:

adb emu kill
emulator -avd Medium_Phone_API_36.0

or

emulator -avd Medium_Phone_API_36.0

2.Start Appium server:

appium

3.In a separate terminal, run your tests:

pytest -s -v tests/test_login.py

---

# find packages locations

adb shell pm list packages

or
adb shell pm list packages | grep chrome
adb shell pm list packages | grep whatsapp
adb shell pm list packages | grep instagram

---

✅ Steps to Open Appium Inspector on macOS
https://github.com/appium/appium-inspector/releases
https://chatgpt.com/share/68d28d05-398c-8009-9e8c-35bf7911df51

✅ Fix

In Appium Inspector → Capability Builder, add these one by one:

Name Type Value
platformName text Android
deviceName text emulator-5554
automationName text UiAutomator2
appPackage text com.meriteye.makeyourjodi
appActivity text com.meriteye.makeyourjodi.MainActivity

⚠️ Do NOT add undefined values (like empty fields).

✅ Then JSON should look like this:
{
"platformName": "Android",
"deviceName": "emulator-5554",
"automationName": "UiAutomator2",
"appPackage": "com.meriteye.makeyourjodi",
"appActivity": "com.meriteye.makeyourjodi.MainActivity"
}

{
"platformName": "Android",
"deviceName": "emulator-5554",
"automationName": "UiAutomator2",
"appPackage": "com.meriteye.makeyourjodi",
"appActivity": ".MainActivity",
"noReset": false,
"autoGrantPermissions": true,
"newCommandTimeout": 300
}

